Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.
Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

post_text:
Attention Triton Families, during these unprecedented times, we are doing our best to develop plans to serve our families and keep everyone safe.

The school will be closed beginning on Wednesday, March 18th through Friday, March 27th as directed by the governor.

Monday and Tuesday school will be open for those that need a place to go. Both days will be non-instructional in nature. Attendance is NOT required. The building will be open for students to pick-up materials during regular business hours.

We will run our buses at the normal time, and students that choose to attend should report to their regular location upon arrival.

Daycare will be open as usual.

All extra-curricular activities including community education are postponed immediately until after March 27th, this includes all practices and rehearsals.

The website www.wearetriton.info will be used to communicate additional information. We will be sending further updates with the calling system as the plan is developed.

FFA ALUMNI MEETING ANNOUNCEMENT:

Hello!

Please mark your calendars for Tuesday, January 2 at 7 pm for our annual Triton FFA Alumni meeting. This meeting will be held in Mr. Ickler's room at the high school.

We will be collecting dues, which is $10.

Tentative agenda:
Treasures Report
Mural
Scholarships
Fundraising

Please feel free to forward this to family and friends or businesses who would be interested in becoming a Triton Alumni FFA member. Remember, this is open to anyone, not only past FFA members.

Let us know if you have any questions. Looking forward to seeing you on January 2.

David Fitzgerald, President
Robby Gilliland, Vice-President
Tim Marquart, Treasurer
Sheryl Dohrmann, Secretary

shared_text:
Dodge County Sheriff MN
November 2, 2019 at 2:02 PM ·

DEPUTY DAVE SKADSON - THANK YOU FOR YOUR SERVICE

Dave Skadson has been a Deputy Sheriff for Dodge County since 2002. He has spent much of his career here serving in both the Triton and Hayfield Schools as our School Resource Officer - originally being assigned to that position by Sheriff Thompson and then a second time by our Administration in 2015. He is currently serving in the schools and has really done a tremendous job with this program and his dedication to the safety and well-being of our community's kids.

Prior to serving here in Dodge County, Dave served our country in the US Navy as an engineer from 1995-1999 on board the aircraft carrier USS John F. Kennedy (CV-67). During his service he completed a 6 month deployment to the Persian Gulf.

Thank you Deputy Skadson for your service to our country, and to our county. We are forever grateful!

Scott

Mr. Boe is consistently sharing the great accomplishments of his students, collaborating with colleagues, and enjoying each day in Cobra Country! Thank you for making THS a great place to learn! Ella was also excited for Mr. Boe and wanted to congratulate him! #WeAreTriton
